BLOEMFONTEIN Celtic defeated National First Division side Mbombela United 2-1 at Dr Petrus Molemela Stadium yesterday to book their place in the quarterfinals of the Nedbank Cup.Celtic striker Abdoul Razak scored a brace to make sure his side joins SuperSport United, Jomo Cosmos, Orlando Pirates, Chippa United, Platinum Stars, Golden Arrows and Kaizer Chiefs in the Last 8 of the Ke Yona cup. Celtic secured their spot in the Last 16 of the cup competition by beating minnows Buya Msuthu 2-0 in the round of 32, while Mbombela hammered Days FC 5-2.Celtic came into this encounter with their confidence on a high following their goalless draw with Mamelodi Sundowns and a 1-0 win over Polokwane City in the league last week. Celtic goalkeeper Ayanda Mtshali was forced to produce a few early saves to keep his side in the game and the visiting side looked threatening in the final third. However, they will be crying over missed chances after conceding in the 25th minute. Razak turned inside the box and slotted in to give the home side a 1-0 lead.Burundian striker Razak continued where he left off in the second half when he bagged his brace in the 55th minute with a beautiful shot inside penalty area to seal the match for the Free State side. The visitors got a consolation goal in the 88th minute when Jermaine Christian headed in.The quarterfinal draw is scheduled for tonight.